# UI003 — ui_no_raw_theme_name
#
# Lint rule: flag raw theme-name string literals like "ios_light", "glass_dark" etc.
# when they appear in call-site code (not inside the dispatch function itself).
#
# Implementation lives in:
#   src/compiler/90.tools/lint/main.spl — Linter.check_ui_raw_theme_name()
#
# Rule logic summary:
#   - Scans every non-comment line for quoted theme-name strings:
#       "ios_light", "ios_dark", "glass_light", "glass_dark",
#       "glass_obsidian_dark", "simple_dark", "simple_light"
#   - If found → emit UI003 warning
#
# Allowlisted paths (never flagged):
#   common/ui/style.spl — UITheme.from_name() match dispatches on runtime text arg;
#                         the literals there are the canonical mapping, not new usage
#   test files (_spec.spl, /test/) — may verify theme-name parsing by design
#
# Suggested fix: use ThemeId.IOSLight / ThemeId.IOSDark / ThemeId.GlassLight /
#                ThemeId.GlassDark / ThemeId.GlassObsidianDark etc. and look up
#                via theme_registry().get(ThemeId.X)
#
# Registration: compiler.tools.lint.main.{all_lint_names, build_default_levels,
#               map_lint_code_to_config_name, Linter.new, Linter.lint_source}
